Theatre of the Mind: Devotional Performance in British Library MS Stowe 39
Johnstone, Boyda. University of Calgary (Canada), ProQuest Dissertations Publishing, 2010. MR69388

Abstract
I examine the relationship between picture and text in the fifteenth-century Middle
English devotional volume, British Library Manuscript Stowe 39. While Stowe 39 has
been previously understood as compiled for religious audiences, I consider textual and
historical evidence in order to propose that it may have been owned by the laity,
specifically women who desired the same level of religious status as monastics. Through
my close examination of the illustrations which accompany the two main texts, The
Abbey of the Holy Ghost and The Desert of Religion, I argue that the female layreader
was able to individually intensify her relationship with God through a deeply embodied,
performative practice of devotion. 

